tafsir[7]{c,v,t}:
  26,160,"The people of Lot cried lies to the Envoys"
  26,164,"I ask of you no wage for this; my wage falls only upon the Lord of all Being."
  26,171,"save an old woman among those that tarried;"
  26,173,"and We rained on them a rain; and evil is the rain of them that are warned."
  26,176,"The men of the Thicket cried lies to the Envoys"
  26,179,"I ask of you no wage for this;"
  26,180,"my wage falls only upon the Lord of all Being."